BLUETONGUE - EUROPE (23): UPDATE
********************************
A ProMED-mail post
<http://www.promedmail.org>
ProMED-mail is a program of the
International Society for Infectious Diseases
<http://www.isid.org>
Date: Sat, 2 Dec 2006
From: ProMED-mail <promed@promedmail.org>
Source: EU, DG Health & Consumer Protection web-site [edited]
<http://ec.europa.eu/food/animal/diseases/adns/table_11_2006/adns_011206_en.pdf>

EU Animal disease notification system (ADNS)
--------------------------------------------
According to the most current weekly update of table 11 (animal
disease situation per country and per disease; distributed 1 Dec
2006), the total number of confirmed bluetongue outbreaks, reported
by European Union member states during the period 1 Jan 2006 to 1 Dec
2006, was 2130 (73 added during the week of 24 Nov to 1 Dec 2006,
compared to 178 added during the week of 17 to 24 Nov 2006, 197 added
during the week of 10-17 Nov and 207 during the week of 3-10 Nov
2006).
The following summarised confirmed 2006 outbreaks are retrieved from
the last (1 Dec 2006) and the 4 previous weekly ADNS reports:
Country/ 1 Dec / 24 Nov /17 Nov / 10 Nov/ 3 Nov / last confirmation date
1. Belgium / 687 /670 /626 / 590 / 490 / 29 Nov 2006
2. Germany / 829 /812 / 744 / 630 / 592 / 27 Nov 2006
3. France / 6 / 6 / 6 / 5 / 5 / 14 Nov 2006
4. Netherlands / 447 / 445 / 437 / 409 / 359 / 29 Nov 2006
5. Bulgaria / 13 / 13 / 13 / 13 / 8 / 5 Nov 2006
6. Italy / 146 /110 / 52 / 35 / 21 / 22 Nov 2006
7. Portugal / 1 / 1 / 1 / 0 / 0 / 14 Nov 2006
